The paper proposes a method that combines multi-task learning and co-evolutionary algorithms to address dynamic time series prediction. This involves the use of neural networks and dynamic programming. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper also involves systems and control theory, which makes cs.SY (Systems and Control) a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with time series data, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
